From: kelivo-win7 <dev@kelivo.local>
Date: 2026-06-29
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] dart: dynamic-load SetFileInformationByHandle with Win7 fallback

Dart SDK 3.12.1 may use SetFileInformationByHandle with
FileRenameInfoEx/FileDispositionInfoEx flags that are only
available on Win10 1607+ for atomic file operations.

Replace with GetProcAddress + fallback to MoveFileEx/DeleteFile
when the extended API is unavailable.

--- a/runtime/bin/file_win.cc
+++ b/runtime/bin/file_win.cc
@@ -XX,XX +XX,XX @@
 // In File::Delete or File::Rename:
-  // Direct call (Win10+)
-  SetFileInformationByHandle(handle,
-                             FileDispositionInfoEx,
-                             &info, sizeof(info));
+  // Win7-compatible dynamic load
+  using SetFileInformationByHandleFunc = BOOL(WINAPI*)(
+      HANDLE, FILE_INFO_BY_HANDLE_CLASS, LPVOID, DWORD);
+  auto SetFileInformationByHandle =
+      reinterpret_cast<SetFileInformationByHandleFunc>(
+          GetProcAddress(GetModuleHandleW(L"kernel32.dll"),
+                         "SetFileInformationByHandle"));
+  if (SetFileInformationByHandle) {
+    SetFileInformationByHandle(handle, FileDispositionInfoEx,
+                               &info, sizeof(info));
+  } else {
+    // Win7: use DeleteFileW / MoveFileExW
+    // ...
+  }

=== How to generate this patch ===
Run in engine/src/dart:
  grep -rn "SetFileInformationByHandle" runtime/bin/file_win.cc
  # If present, edit to add dynamic-load wrapper
  # If not present (3.12.1 doesn't use it), delete this patch
  # and remove from engine_patches/series